"]}]},{"name":"Tessin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: habitational name from any of several places so named in Mecklenburg."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margrethe","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margarete","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margrethe von Tessin was born in 1452, in Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany, her father, Curt von Tessin, was 42 and her mother, Mrs Curt von Tessin, was 45. She had at least 1 son and 4 daughters with Jakob Kannengeter. She died in 1476, in her hometown, at the age of 24."},"et":{"1452–1476":"1452–1476","1450–1528":"1450–1528","1397–Female":"1397–Surnud","1470–Female":"1470–Surnud","1472–Male":"1472–Surnud","1474–Female":"1474–Surnud","1476–Female":"1476–Surnud","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1408–Female":"1408–Surnud","abt. 1474":"umbes 1474","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","abt. 1476":"umbes 1476","1470":"1470","abt. 1470":"umbes 1470","abt. 1472":"umbes 1472","1476":"1476","1410":"1410","1452":"1452","1474":"1474","1397":"1397","1408":"1408","1528":"1528","of, GREIFSWALD,POMMERN,PREUSSEN":"Greifswald, Pommern, Preußen, Saksamaa","of Greifswald, Pmmrn, Prss.":"Greifswald, Pommern, Preußen, Saksamaa","Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Tyskland":"Greifswald, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1452–1476":"1452–1476","1450–1528":"1450–1528","1397–Female":"1397–Kuollut","1470–Female":"1470–Kuollut","1472–Male":"1472–Kuollut","1474–Female":"1474–Kuollut","1476–Female":"1476–Kuollut","1410–Male":"1410–Kuollut","1408–Female":"1408–Kuollut","abt. 1474":"noin 1474","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","abt. 1476":"noin 1476","1470":"1470","abt. 14